Token.Abstract: A map of attribute values as they appeared before the UpdateItem operation. This map only appears if ReturnValues was specified as something other than NONE in the request. Each element represents one attribute.

The capacity units consumed by an operation. The data returned includes the total provisioned throughput consumed, along with statistics for the table and any indexes involved in the operation. ConsumedCapacity is only returned if the request asked for it. For more information, see Provisioned Throughput in the Amazon DynamoDB Developer Guide.
